Lets learn about Media Queries today.

#Media query
-A media query in CSS is a technique used to apply different styles to a webpage based on the characteristics of the device or screen being used to view it 
â€”such as screen width, height, resolution, orientation, or even color depth.
-Syntax:
@media media-type and (condition) {
  /* CSS rules here */
}

Ex:
@media (width : 600px) {
    div {
    background-color : red;
    }
}

#Common Media Features
| Feature       | Description                | Example                  |
| ------------- | -------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `max-width`   | Max screen width           | `max-width: 768px`       |
| `min-width`   | Min screen width           | `min-width: 1024px`      |
| `orientation` | Portrait or landscape mode | `orientation: landscape` |
| `max-height`  | Max screen height          | `max-height: 500px`      |
| `resolution`  | Screen resolution (DPI)    | `min-resolution: 300dpi` |

#Multiple Conditions Example
@media screen and (min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 900px) {
  .menu {
    font-size: 18px;
  }
}
